<br>
Time for a new tactic.<br>
<br>
Wizards, Mages, Necros could give a +5%exp modifyer to the group. 5% is not all that much, it's what, 2 or 3 BoT mobs less per AA when you are killing 50 of them.  But it's enough for other classes to want these classes in groups, without having to prove to the entire EQ community that we have a group use. When people look at the LFG, they look at utility.  And frankly, Evac, Ports and Sight spells aren't utility that's looked for anymore. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=faramir42>Faramir42</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 99<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/15/03 9:30 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Another grouping idea...</span><hr size=1> Only that every other class would want this. I'm not saying it's a bad idea. But what would be the reasoning behind it other then to have a little xp? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fqubedf3povar>FqubedF3povar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 160<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/15/03 10:24 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Another grouping idea...</span><hr size=1> Good idea tho every class would want it, like fara said. I would suggest giving us also a 5% solo bonus seeing as we do that alot but that might get to be counterproductive....<br>
<br>
Oh well, ppl will still see your dmg every now and then.<br>
<br>
F3 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=annoid>Annoid</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 63<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/15/03 11:22 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Another grouping idea...</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> Only that every other class would want this. I'm not saying it's a bad idea. But what would be the reasoning behind it other then to have a little xp?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->The reasoning would be to give us something to offer groups on an exclusive basis so we get into them more readily. The trinity classes all offer something that is needed in groups, for the group to function. We don't. We can't put out as much damage on a sustained basis as other melee damage dealers can, due to both mana limitations and aggro factors, and as has been said, people don't look for Evac'ers/porters as a high priority. With corpses popping in the GY in a short time, and a 96% rez a certainty (who hunts planes without a 56+ cleric?) who the hell needs an evac'er? Grps pick what is best for the existing grp as it is, and that's not us at this time.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zuratuli>Zuratuli</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 270<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/15/03 5:30 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Another grouping idea...</span><hr size=1> If your a <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>good</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> wizard you will be upping the group's dps anyways thus increasing xp over time... which is basically an xp bonus <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=69194"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://people.ucsc.edu/~arice/pictures/zuratulisig.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=annoid>Annoid</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 65<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/15/03 9:28 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Another grouping idea...</span><hr size=1> But we don't increase the group's damage output on a sustained basis as much as other classes do. So the other classes get priority for groups. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rombusmindspire>Rombus Mindspire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><table width=111><tr><td style=filter:glow(color=#6633FF strength=1);font-family:arial;font-weight;bold;font-size:'1pt' nowrap><font size=1 color=#FFFFFF face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif>Forum Tyrant<br><br>Owned by Ikeya<BR>Destroying EverWars...<BR><a href=mailto:rombus@graffe.com style=text-decoration: none><u>Contact Rombus</u></font></td></tr></table></span><br>  Posts: 7290<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/15/03 11:33 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Another grouping idea...</span><hr size=1> Over time you'll find that with a Wizard in the group you'll gain more experience.  Sustained DPS may not be a strength of ours but burst DPS is.  If mobs are dying faster you can pull more meaning more EXP.  Sustained DPS is great and all, don't get me wrong, but you'll find your EXP income is better when you have at least 1 burst damage dealer in the group.<br>
<br>
On a side note I do like this idea but it would need tweaking.  Interesting solution as well! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zuratuli>Zuratuli</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 273<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/16/03 12:49 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Another grouping idea...</span><hr size=1> In XP groups I almost never go near Oom.. Its almost impossible... my sustained dps is equal to my burst dps which is equal to how much aggro the tank can hold... When giants die in 1 minute you can only do so much damage without taking aggro though.<br>
<br>
I do have 25 selfbuffed mana regen though. Throw in VoQ and PoT9 and I'm at 51 mana regen while XPing and can usually use horse. HoD and Harvest.. half the time I do not even bother using.<br>
<br>
What this means is for the lesser equipped players this might be good... but it also applies to the ubers which means they will be getting alot more xp than they were before which already is alot more than the lesser equipped players. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=69194"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://people.ucsc.edu/~arice/pictures/zuratulisig.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showPrevMessage?topicID=929.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showNextMessage?topicID=929.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.emailToFriend?topicID=929.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.threadControl?topicID=929.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=929.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=929.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies">